<refentry id="test_config">
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>test_config</refentrytitle>
    <manvolnum>1</manvolnum>
  </refmeta>

  <refnamediv>
    <refname>test_config</refname>
    <refpurpose>
      test the configuration file on syntax errors.
    </refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>test_config</command>
      <arg>-v?</arg>
      <arg>-d <replaceable>level</replaceable></arg>
      <arg>-f <replaceable>configfile</replaceable></arg>
      <arg>--usage</arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      This simple utility might be used in order to test the syntaxtical
      correctness of a &ps; configuration file.
    </para>
    <para>
      Since looking up error messages of the &ps; daemon <xref linkend="psid"/>
      from the <citerefentry>
	<refentrytitle>syslog</refentrytitle>
	<manvolnum>3</manvolnum>
      </citerefentry> is usually not very convenient, the same error messages
      also might be produced by this tool but simply send to the stderr.
    </para>
    <para>
      The correct syntax of the &ps; configuration file might be looked up in
      the corresponding manual page <xref linkend="parastation_conf"/>.
    </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Options</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <option>-d</option>
	  <option>, --debug=<replaceable>level</replaceable></option>
        </term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>Activate the debugging mode and set the debug level to
	    <replaceable>level</replaceable>.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <option>-f</option>
	  <option>, --file=<replaceable>file</replaceable></option>
        </term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>Choose <replaceable>file</replaceable> to be the &ps;
	    configuration file to parse. The default is to use
	    <filename>/etc/parastation.conf</filename>.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <option>-v</option>
	  <option>, --version</option>
        </term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>Output version information and exit.</para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <option>-?</option>
	  <option>, --help</option>
        </term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>Show a help message.</para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
	  <option>--usage</option>
	</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Display a brief usage message.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>See also</title>
    <para>
      <xref linkend="parastation_conf"/>, <xref linkend="psid"/>
    </para>
  </refsect1>
</refentry>
